the horses, back up there ways.

284
00:47:30,480 --> 00:47:31,999
Okay, let's see it.

285
00:47:55,440 --> 00:47:56,479
Hold it right there!

286
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:58,359
Boss!

287
00:48:08,400 --> 00:48:09,319
Get down of that horse.

288
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:14,159
I said get down of that horse!

289
00:48:34,920 --> 00:48:35,759
Cobb!

290
00:50:05,680 --> 00:50:07,279
How close are we to Falcon's Peak?

291
00:50:07,480 --> 00:50:09,199
This is Falcon's Peak.

292
00:50:09,640 --> 00:50:14,039
You want to find your kin? You go find them.
I ain't helping you. This is horseshit.

293
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:17,319
What's happening?

294
00:50:19,960 --> 00:50:21,119
Let's go!

295
00:51:08,320 --> 00:51:11,679
McKinley / Johnson
Mining Company

296
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:16,999
Cobb, get him! Get him!

297
00:51:27,280 --> 00:51:29,319
Don't you move, son-of-a-bitch!

298
00:51:31,280 --> 00:51:33,719
- What the hell is going on?
- What does it look like?

299
00:51:34,200 --> 00:51:35,879
Looks like you're a goddamn liar.

300
00:51:38,120 --> 00:51:39,919
- Tie him up and drag him.
- No.

301
00:51:54,960 --> 00:51:57,959
Don't you touch him!
Don't you touch him!

302
00:52:08,480 --> 00:52:11,039
Damn, god damn you!

303
00:53:26,720 --> 00:53:28,439
You ain't dead yet?

304
00:53:32,680 --> 00:53:35,119
Hey son-of-a-bitch, 
I'm talking to you.

305
00:53:48,600 --> 00:53:51,559
Hey drunkard, you want a drink?

306
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:07,999
- Look at this.
- Come on, move it down.

307
00:54:08,840 --> 00:54:09,799
Warning!

308
00:54:10,560 --> 00:54:12,799
McKinley / Johnson
Mining Company

309
00:54:13,360 --> 00:54:14,999
Give me a hand.

310
00:54:16,000 --> 00:54:17,599
I got it.

311
00:54:19,560 --> 00:54:20,959
I got it, I got it.

312
00:54:21,720 --> 00:54:22,679
Wait up. Watch it!

313
00:54:31,920 --> 00:54:32,879
There, Roscoe.

314
00:54:35,080 --> 00:54:36,439
Hurry up, Roscoe.

315
00:54:56,360 --> 00:54:58,399
Son-of-a-bitch.

316
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:01,639
- That old man was right.
- Damn!

317
00:55:02,560 --> 00:55:04,119
How much you figure we got here?

318
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:05,999
More than enough!

319
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:13,959
Look at this.

320
00:55:22,840 --> 00:55:25,359
- I can not believe!
- Have you seen?

321
00:55:26,280 --> 00:55:28,279
This is gold!

322
00:55:41,720 --> 00:55:43,239
Pure gold.

323
00:55:49,240 --> 00:55:50,439
Go.

324
00:56:21,040 --> 00:56:23,199
Let's start get this on the horses.

325
00:56:23,720 --> 00:56:25,119
I ain't leaving.

326
00:56:33,040 --> 00:56:34,319
Come on, move it!

327
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:36,079
Move it!

328
00:56:50,320 --> 00:56:51,479
Boss!

329
00:56:51,920 --> 00:56:54,319
Boss! That Indian is gone!

330
00:56:54,760 --> 00:56:56,359
Boss, that Indian is gone!

331
00:56:56,960 --> 00:56:58,199
Boss!

332
00:56:58,600 --> 00:57:00,399
That Indian is gone.

333
00:57:07,320 --> 00:57:10,279
Damn it! Go find him before 
he brings more back here.

334
00:57:10,440 --> 00:57:13,639
We ain't going nowhere until
we work out a split.

335
00:57:14,120 --> 00:57:15,799
There is plenty of gold.

336
00:57:15,960 --> 00:57:19,439
Yeah Farley, with Billy's take,
there is more for all of us.

337
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:22,839
He has been buried just 15 minutes. 
And you already are taking his cut?

338
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:24,239
He's dead. He can't use it.

339
00:57:24,960 --> 00:57:28,079
You're wasting time!
Go find that Indian!

340
00:57:31,600 --> 00:57:33,039
What the hell are you doing?

341
00:57:33,880 --> 00:57:35,999
That Indian is gonna have
running us around in circles.

342
00:57:38,480 --> 00:57:39,439
Get him up.

343
00:57:45,840 --> 00:57:47,999
I need him to get me back here.

344
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:54,159
They never gonna find him.

345
00:57:57,200 --> 00:57:59,439
And he's gonna come back and kill you.

346
00:59:35,640 --> 00:59:36,999
I don't trust Max.

347
00:59:37,160 --> 00:59:40,479
If he tries anything, 
it'll be the last thing he does.

348
00:59:40,640 --> 00:59:42,999
Relax Farley, we'll get back to camp.

349
00:59:43,440 --> 00:59:45,919
If he's still to camp,
we'll take Max.

350
00:59:46,520 --> 00:59:47,959
We've gone far enough.

351
00:59:48,800 --> 00:59:50,599
I'm going back for the gold.

352
00:59:54,160 --> 00:59:55,959
Come on, Mr. Hanner.

353
01:00:00,120 --> 01:00:01,439
Me and you here.

354
01:00:04,040 --> 01:00:05,839
Get up!

355
01:00:09,280 --> 01:00:10,679
What?

356
01:00:13,120 --> 01:00:14,279
You want a gun, Hanner?

357
01:00:16,720 --> 01:00:18,159
Get the hell up, Hanner!

358
01:00:19,920 --> 01:00:20,919
You want this?

359
01:00:22,320 --> 01:00:23,959
Here you go.

360
01:00:24,800 --> 01:00:26,039
You want it?

361
01:00:26,800 --> 01:00:27,639
What do you want?

362
01:00:28,680 --> 01:00:30,119
I want your blood.

363
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:13,199
- Where the hell have you been?
- We couldn't find our way back.

364
01:01:19,240 --> 01:01:20,479
Where is Hanner?

365
01:01:22,240 --> 01:01:23,039
He's dead.

366
01:01:31,640 --> 01:01:32,919
Where is the gold?

367
01:01:33,720 --> 01:01:35,959
I got as many bags
I can out of there.

368
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:39,479
Tomorrow morning you can get your 
fat ass in there and get the rest.

369
01:01:45,880 --> 01:01:49,679
I can't figure out why they didn't 
come back for that gold.

370
01:01:52,720 --> 01:01:54,359
They never left.

371
01:01:58,160 --> 01:01:59,679
They died here.

372
01:02:03,080 --> 01:02:05,399
They caught the white man's disease.

373
01:02:05,600 --> 01:02:07,039
Shut up.

374
01:02:07,760 --> 01:02:12,199
The only one I can't cure, 
the only one the Indians are immune to.

375
01:02:15,040 --> 01:02:19,199
The Indians were right.
You got the fever for yellow rock.

376
01:02:19,400 --> 01:02:21,759
- There ain't no such thing.
- Yes, there is!

377
01:02:21,960 --> 01:02:22,879
- There ain't!
- Yes, there is!

378
01:02:23,080 --> 01:02:24,039
There ain't no such thing!

379
01:02:24,200 --> 01:02:27,079
- I told you to shut up.
- You shut up!

380
01:02:27,720 --> 01:02:29,439
Let me tell you something.

381
01:02:29,600 --> 01:02:32,919
The Indians say, 
when the white man came,

382
01:02:33,480 --> 01:02:35,879
they opened a wound
in that mountain.

383
01:02:36,040 --> 01:02:37,039
They cut its veins.

384
01:02:38,120 --> 01:02:40,039
And he mountain bled.

385
01:02:40,840 --> 01:02:44,679
And the caught the fever.
They were riddled with it.

386
01:02:47,200 --> 01:02:49,119
I see the symptoms.

387
01:02:49,360 --> 01:02:50,799
In all of you.

388
01:02:52,240 --> 01:02:53,839
It makes you sweat,

389
01:02:54,040 --> 01:02:55,639
it makes you a headache.

390
01:02:57,120 --> 01:03:00,199
You can't think of anything 
else but the gold.

391
01:03:01,640 --> 01:03:02,599
You feel it?

392
01:03:03,360 --> 01:03:05,439
I see it in all of you.

393
01:03:05,840 --> 01:03:08,519
You're just trying to take 
that gold out of the mountain.

394
01:03:08,680 --> 01:03:10,759
And you won't make it down alive.

395
01:03:11,440 --> 01:03:12,799
You hear me?

396
01:03:14,360 --> 01:03:15,959
You got it the worst.

397
01:03:16,160 --> 01:03:17,959
There is no curing you.

398
01:03:18,160 --> 01:03:19,119
No curing you!

399
01:03:20,200 --> 01:03:23,399
Keep your goddamn mouth shut!

400
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:30,079
You're all gonna die here.

401
01:03:30,560 --> 01:03:32,199
You hear me?

402
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:01,839
Hey, boss.

403
01:04:03,160 --> 01:04:05,399
What she said last night 
about that curse...

404
01:04:06,760 --> 01:04:08,399
You think there is
anything to it?

405
01:04:08,920 --> 01:04:10,839
What the hell are you talking about?

406
01:04:11,480 --> 01:04:14,919
The gold...
Why ain't nobody come back for it?

407
01:04:16,520 --> 01:04:20,839
Because those jackasses probably got killed 
by the Indians and they left it behind.

408
01:04:23,320 --> 01:04:25,119
Go tend to those horses.

409
01:04:26,760 --> 01:04:28,119
Yes, sir.

410
01:04:34,400 --> 01:04:35,959
You're gonna do what you said?

411
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:39,759
Just load the gold on, 
and I'll kill them all.

412
01:05:04,520 --> 01:05:05,479
Get your ass up here.

413
01:05:31,160 --> 01:05:41,559
Shit!

414
01:05:49,400 --> 01:05:50,879
I need some water.

415
01:05:52,760 --> 01:05:54,519
Can I have some water, please?

416
01:05:57,880 --> 01:05:59,239
Please.

417
01:06:20,920 --> 01:06:22,039
You're limping.

418
01:06:23,320 --> 01:06:25,759
A goddamn horse stepped on my foot.

419
01:06:27,200 --> 01:06:30,839
If you untie me I can help you.
I'll take a look at it.

420
01:06:39,240 --> 01:06:40,919
I can't do that, ma'am.

421
01:06:45,560 --> 01:06:49,639
You need to untie me.
Let me go, I didn't do anything.

422
01:06:50,720 --> 01:06:54,239
I don't deserve to die.
Roscoe, let me go.

423
01:06:54,400 --> 01:06:57,719
You are not like the other ones.
Let me go.

424
01:07:02,680 --> 01:07:04,239
Get up here.

425
01:07:20,080 --> 01:07:21,439
I'm sorry, boss.

426
01:07:23,520 --> 01:07:24,839
I got a horse get away from me.

427
01:07:25,040 --> 01:07:27,879
Never mind the goddamn horse.
Get the rest of those bags.

428
01:07:28,040 --> 01:07:29,039
Yes, sir.

